    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-05-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="658"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Cambon</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-05-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 31.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: With reference to the inquiries as to the
                    situation of the master and crew of the captured Spanish steamer <hi
                        rend="italic">Panama</hi>, I have the honor to inform you that instructions
                    have been sent to the authorities of the United States at Key West to transmit
                    to the proper authorities of the United States in this capital any open letters
                    addressed by the officers and crew of the steamer in question to their families,
                    to the end that such letters may be forwarded to their destination through your
                    embassy.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
